x,y,z
\frac{dx}{x^{2}+a^{2}}=\frac{dy}{xy-az}=\frac{dz}{xz+ay}
z = ky
k
k = \pm i
k=i
z = ky
z=k(y)y
 \begin{align} \frac{dy}{xy-az} & = \frac{dz}{xz+ay}\\ \frac{dy/y}{x-a (z/y)} & = \frac{dz/z}{x+a (y/z)} \end{align} 
 \begin{align} \frac{dy/y}{x-a k} & = \frac{dy/y}{x+a/k} \end{align} 
\begin{align} \frac{dx}{x^2 + a^2} & = \frac{dy/y}{x - ia}\\ \frac{dx}{x + ia} & = \frac{dy}{y}\\ y & = c(x + ia) \end{align} 
 \begin{align} z & = ic(x+ia)\\ y & = c(x+ia) \end{align} 
 \begin{align} z & = -ic(x-ia)\\ y & = c(x-ia) \end{align} 
\frac{dy}{dx}=\frac{xy-az}{x^{2}+a^{2}}
\frac{dz}{dx}=\frac{xz+ay}{x^{2}+a^{2}}
